-- Japan Chip, Flat-Screen Gear Demand May Fall 11% in Fiscal 2012
-- B y   Y o s h i n o r i   E k i
-- 2012-01-10T08:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-10/japan-chip-flat-screen-gear-demand-may-fall-11-in-fiscal-2012.html
Global demand for equipment from
Japanese makers used to make semiconductors and flat displays is
expected to fall 11% next fiscal year, an industry group said.  Machinery sales will decline to 1.32 trillion yen ($17
billion) in the 12 months beginning April, from 1.48 trillion
yen a year earlier, according to a forecast released by
Semiconductor Equipment Association of  Japan  today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Yoshinori Eki in Tokyo at 
